snippet.textDisplay:
Taetae isn't angry or intimidating he's nervous and uncomfotable! uwu

I think because he just finds the whole talking in English thing super scary; he keeps clenching his fists and biting his lips and looking down/avoiding eye contact, especially when asked things he might be called on to answer, like what music they're listening to these days. (He's always listening to cool new music and loves to share that with us so there was a high chance he'd be expected to give an answer so he basically curled in on himself to avoid having to). He keeps holding his hand up over his mouth/fidgeting at his neck and holding his arm literally across his body as a barrier against the discomfort/the possiblity someone's about to expect an English answer from him, and he only really relaxes when he the interviewer is speaking/someone else finishes answering instead because then an expectation to answer in English isn't posssibly imminent. He even crosses his arms which is the classic universal sign for closed body language indicating discomfort/wanting to create a barrier.

In conclusion taetae scared not scary 🥺
